In order to install a x64 compiler with Visual Studio Express 2010 you may want to read first:

* http://stackoverflow.com/questions/19366006/error-when-installing-windows-sdk-7-1
* http://stackoverflow.com/questions/1901279/windows-7-sdk-installation-failure
* http://stackoverflow.com/questions/1865069/how-to-compile-a-64-bit-application-using-visual-c-2010-express
* http://stackoverflow.com/questions/8044385/64-bit-build-on-microsoft-visual-c-express-2010

In summary you need to install (uninstall everything if needed) in this order:
1. VS2010 C++ Express
2. SDK 7.1
3. VS2010 SP1
4. SP1 Compiler patch KB2519277

After Step 4, you'll find cl.exe at:

C:/Program Files/Microsoft Visual Studio 10.0/VC/bin/cl.exe
C:/Program Files/Microsoft Visual Studio 10.0/VC/bin/x86_amd64/cl.exe

